RACE.RACE_TEXT: TURF PARADISE RACE 3 1M Turf CR: 77. Claiming Purse 12400. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since April 1 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $8,500. Arizona Bred Claiming Price $10,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: FAT AND FURIOUS lacked early speed, checked nearing the three-eighths marker, moved five-wide through the second turn, reached the fore with a furlong to run and drew off as a handy winner. CURIOUS INJI broke sharply to press the pace while racing four-wide, stayed on well in the drive and came back to regain the place. PANCAKES AND BEER stalked the leaders from between foes, moved up to take command nearing the half, opened a clear lead into the stretch but was no match for the winner in the drive. IMPULSUS raced unhurried early, moved three-wide through the second turn, drifted in and out in mid-stretch and lacked the needed rally. EARLYNTHEMORN sprinted clear at once, saved ground while setting the pace and weakened after going a half. THE RACE WAS HAND TIMED.
